  "slug": "date-squares",
  "title": "Date squares",
  "subtitle": "Oat traybake with sticky date filling",
  "excerpt": "A traybake with a buttery oat base and crumble top sandwiching a thick, sweet date paste. Simple to make, keeps well for a week, and cuts into neat squares.",
  "type": "RECIPE",
  "sourceNotes": "Date squares (also known as matrimonial cake in Canada) appear in British and Canadian domestic cookery from the early twentieth century. The formula (an oat and butter crumble layer sandwiching a cooked date filling) is consistent across regional variants. This version follows the standard British domestic formula.",
  "body": {
    "type": "doc",
    "content": [
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Date squares are built in three steps: cook the date filling, make the oat mixture, assemble. The filling and the oat base both have the same ten-minute prep; the oven does the rest. Cut only when fully cooled, the filling is liquid while warm and the squares crumble if you rush it.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "ingredientsList",
        "content": [
          {
            "type": "ingredientsGroup",
            "attrs": {
              "title": "Date filling"
            },
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "dried-dates",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": "pitted, roughly chopped",
                  "quantity": 300,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "lemon-juice",
                  "unit": "tbsp",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 1,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "type": "ingredientsGroup",
            "attrs": {
              "title": "Oat base and crumble"
            },
            "content": [
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "porridge-oats",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 200,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "plain-flour",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 200,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "light-brown-sugar",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 150,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "fine-sea-salt",
                  "unit": "tsp",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 0.5,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "bicarbonate-of-soda",
                  "unit": "tsp",
                  "prepNote": null,
                  "quantity": 0.5,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              },
              {
                "type": "ingredient",
                "attrs": {
                  "slug": "unsalted-butter",
                  "unit": "g",
                  "prepNote": "cold, cubed",
                  "quantity": 200,
                  "isOptional": false
                }
              }
            ]
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 2
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Method",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Cook the date filling",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Put the {{dried-dates}} in a small saucepan with 150 ml of water and the {{lemon-juice}}. Cook over medium heat, stirring, for 8 to 10 minutes until the dates break down into a thick ",
            "type": "text"
          },
          {
            "text": "paste",
            "type": "text",
            "marks": [
              {
                "type": "glossaryTooltip",
                "attrs": {
                  "termId": "cmpaefqlz0000bkv4t8tj21x0"
                }
              }
            ]
          },
          {
            "text": ". Remove from the heat and leave to cool.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Prepare",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Heat the oven to 180°C fan. Grease a 20×20 cm tin and line with baking paper.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Make the oat mixture",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Mix the {{porridge-oats}}, {{plain-flour}}, {{light-brown-sugar}}, {{fine-sea-salt}}, and {{bicarbonate-of-soda}} in a large bowl. Add the cold {{unsalted-butter}}. Rub it in with your fingertips until the mixture forms rough, crumbly clumps.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "heading",
        "attrs": {
          "level": 3
        },
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Assemble and bake, 25 to 30 minutes",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      },
      {
        "type": "paragraph",
        "content": [
          {
            "text": "Press half the oat mixture into the base of the tin in a firm, even layer. Spread the date paste over it, reaching the edges. Scatter the remaining oat mixture on top and press it down gently. Bake for 25 to 30 minutes until the top is golden. Cool completely in the tin before cutting into squares.",
            "type": "text"
          }
        ]
      }
    ]
  },
